Area of rectangle,
$$
\begin{aligned}
A &=2 x \cdot 2 \sqrt{r^{2}-x^{2}} \\
&=4 x \sqrt{r^{2}-x^{2}} \\
\frac{d A}{d x} &=\frac{4\left(r^{2}-2 x^{2}\right)}{\sqrt{r^{2}-x^{2}}}
\end{aligned}
$$
For maximum or minimum put $\frac{d A}{d x}=0$
$$
\Rightarrow \quad x=r / \sqrt{2}
$$
It can be easily checked that $\frac{d^{2} A}{d x^{2}} < 0$ for this value of $x$. $\therefore A$ is maximum for $x=\frac{r}{\sqrt{2}}$ and the maximum value of $A$ is given by
$$
A=4 \frac{r}{\sqrt{2}} \sqrt{r^{2}-\frac{r^{2}}{2}}=2 r^{2}
$$

$\begin{aligned} & \text {Let } f(x)=x^4 y^4 \\ & \text { And } a^2 x^4+b^2 y^4=c^6 \\ & \Rightarrow y^4=\frac{1}{b^2}\left(c^6-a^2 x^4\right) \\ & \therefore \quad f(x)=\mathrm{x}^4 \cdot \frac{1}{b^2}\left(c^6-a^2 x^4\right) \\ & =\frac{1}{b^2} x^4\left(c^6-a^2 x^4\right) \\ & f^{\prime}(x)=\frac{1}{b^2}\left(4 x^{3 c^6}-8 a^2 x^7\right) \\ & \end{aligned}$
for extrem point:
$\begin{aligned}
& f^{\prime}(\mathrm{x})=0 \Rightarrow 4 x^3\left(c^6-2 a^2 x^4\right)=0 \\
& \Rightarrow x=0 \text { or } x^4=\frac{c^6}{2 a^2}
\end{aligned}$
For maxima : $x=\frac{c^6}{2 a^2}$
$\therefore$ The maximum value is :
$\begin{aligned}
& f\left(x=\left(\frac{c^6}{2 a^2}\right)^{\frac{1}{4}}\right) \\
& =\frac{c^6}{2 a^2} \cdot \frac{1}{b^2}\left[c^6-a^2 \cdot \frac{c^6}{2 a^2}\right] \\
& =\frac{c^6}{2 a^2 b^2} \cdot \frac{c^6}{2}=\frac{c^{12}}{4 a^2 b^2}
\end{aligned}$

